title: SFH on eHealth record system and human swine flu vaccine
content_text:
p>
Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the 
Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, at a stand-up media session 
after attending the opening ceremony of eHealth Forum 2009 today (October 
8): Reporter: (About eHealth record system) Secretary for Food and Health: Today we are launching the initiation of a 
partnership driving initiative, that is asking for any suggestions and 
proposals from the health care as well as the IT sectors. Whoever is 
interested in being a partner of this project will be able to show the

interested in being a partner of this project will be able to show the 
interest. We have a set of documents that they can actually take home. And 
they can also consider whether they would like to give any information to 
us. We will gather this as soon as possible. And we will be able to, 
perhaps, initiate some partnership projects in the coming months. Reporter: (About eHealth record system) Secretary for Food and Health: We are trying to use the Hong Kong ID card as 
an authorising vehicle for any individual who would like to authorise the

an authorising vehicle for any individual who would like to authorise the 
use of the medical records by their health care providers. So this is 
something that we hope we can actually start piloting. We will start 
piloting next year, perhaps in certain areas, but the whole system will not 
be in place until 2013. Reporter: (How to ensure the privacy) Secretary for Food and Health: We will do consultation in 2010 regarding the 
privacy issue. We also look at the legal side as well to see when and how we

privacy issue. We also look at the legal side as well to see when and how we 
can legislate the protection of privacy in health care records. Reporter: (Human swine flu vaccine) Secretary for Food and Health: We are processing the tender right now. We 
are confident that we are able to get the available vaccine by the end of 
the year, so that we can do the vaccination programme before the start of 
the so-called "winter surge". (Please also refer to the
the so-called "winter surge". (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript)
